cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper is focused on natural language processing and machine learning, specifically analyzing biases in contextual word representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses state-of-the-art models and algorithms, which suggests that it could also fit into cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for assessing bias, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses biases related to race and intersectionality, which could potentially fit into cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
